## batches.toml Generation Rules

For every batch in every RUNNER spec, generate a `[[batch]]` entry:

```toml
[[batch]]
id = "R2_A01"
title = "Document current init template and config data flow"
group = "2A"
deps = []
scope = []                          # Context-only batches have empty scope
also_read = [
    "crates/roko-cli/src/commands/init.rs",
    "crates/roko-core/src/config.rs",
    "crates/roko-cli/src/commands/config_cmd.rs",
    "crates/roko-cli/src/run.rs"
]
verify = "quick"
```

Rules:
- `scope` = the "Write scope" from the runner spec (files the batch MODIFIES)
  - For context-only batches (Type: Context-only): scope = `[]` but add the write target to also_read
    since context-only batches write to `tmp/runners/` not to source code
- `also_read` = the "Read" files from the runner spec
- `deps` = within-runner deps (prefixed) PLUS cross-runner deps from the dependency map above
- `verify` = `"quick"` for most batches
- `group` = `"{runner_number}{group_letter}"` (e.g., "2A", "3B", "6C")

